ctures. These bridges\ncan become kinematically quiescent, when the velocity components of the\ncolliding flows eliminate each other. However, the gas in bridges still\ncontributes to stellar accretion later. Our results demonstrate: bridge-like\nstructures are a transient phenomenon of stellar multiple formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Jul 2019 18:00:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-21"}
