 that can be fitted with fractional\nrheology models. The hydrogels possess rheo-thinning properties with\nsecond-scale recovery. We also show that ionic strength is not only necessary,\nas one could expect, to control the interactions in the lamellar phase but,\nmost importantly, it directly controls the elastic properties of the lamellar\ngels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Jul 2019 05:23:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Dec 2019 14:58:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 18 Dec 2019 05:54:13 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 26 Feb 2020 14:44:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-27"}
