ing\nvoltage according to environmental pressure and temperature variations, to\nachieve constant gain over time. This development answers to a more general\nneed. In fact, voltage compensation is always a requirement for the stability\nof gaseous detectors and its need is enhanced in multi-layer ones.\n  In this paper, the HV system and its performance are described in details, as\nwell as the stability of the novel MPGD-based photon detectors during the\nphysics data taking at COMPASS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Jul 2019 13:06:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-18"}
